{
  "stem": "2590.2",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was 20-years-old at the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, what shall I do?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said listen, I respected your parents very, very much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I will do anything for you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you are only 20, but you're mature enough.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And even if your-- your parents would be alive, they wouldn't be able to tell you what to do.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You have to do what your instinct tells you.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and sure enough, we got married, and we came to Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then from Poland, we were also smuggled through.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The Haganah smuggled us through to Czechoslovakia, to Asch.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we came to Munich.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And not far from Munich there was displace camp, Foehrenwald.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we came to Foehrenwald.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you know, there were many camps in Germany, because the Jews didn't have where to go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, I forgot to tell.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I came back to Rovno, and I met some friends that I went together to school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they said to me-- they started to cross themselves-- and said, you still alive?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You still alive?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And many of them said Hitler did not do a good job.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the welcome.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we knew that we can not remain in Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And didn't know where to go,",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the only way to-- the only place to go was Palestine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that time they were called this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because Israel, Palestine also and the English mandate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they did not let the Jews in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the Haganah smuggled us-- smuggled through.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- and we were in Foehrenwald.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we got married.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you know, we used to meet and decide what we do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of us-- the majority of us-- were afraid to have children, because we were afraid another Holocaust surely come.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I decided again, we said, gosh.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
